    "body": "\n## Purpose\n\nFor some reason in https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/29213 this pathway wasn't enabled by default when it seems like a +10% improvement at low batch and even with DeepGEMM at large batch.\n\nLet's see if we break anything putting this on by default.\n\n## Test Plan\n\n## Test Result\n\nCommands on 4xH100:\n```\nchg run -g=4 -- vllm serve MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.5 -tp=4 --load-format=dummy --trust-remote-code --max-model-len auto\nvllm bench serve \\\n  --backend openai-chat \\\n  --model MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.5 \\\n  --dataset-name random \\\n  --random-input-len 1024 \\\n  --random-output-len 512 \\\n  --num-prompts 64 \\\n  --max-concurrency 8 \\\n  --endpoint /v1/chat/completions\n```\n\nBefore:\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     64\nFailed requests:                         0\nMaximum request concurrency:             8\nBenchmark duration (s):                  36.56\nTotal input tokens:                      65536\nTotal generated tokens:                  32768\nRequest throughput (req/s):              1.75\nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         896.22\nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    960.00\nPeak concurrent requests:                16.00\nTotal token throughput (tok/s):          2688.66\n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          234.29\nMedian TTFT (ms):                        246.07\nP99 TTFT (ms):                           340.46\n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          8.48\nMedian TPOT (ms):                        8.40\nP99 TPOT (ms):                           8.84\n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           8.49\nMedian ITL (ms):                         8.40\nP99 ITL (ms):                            9.36\n==================================================\n```\n\nAfter:\n```\n============ Serving Benchmark Result ============\nSuccessful requests:                     64\nFailed requests:                         0\nMaximum request concurrency:             8\nBenchmark duration (s):                  33.83\nTotal input tokens:                      65536\nTotal generated tokens:                  32768\nRequest throughput (req/s):              1.89\nOutput token throughput (tok/s):         968.47\nPeak output token throughput (tok/s):    1040.00\nPeak concurrent requests:                16.00\nTotal token throughput (tok/s):          2905.41\n---------------Time to First Token----------------\nMean TTFT (ms):                          240.44\nMedian TTFT (ms):                        248.23\nP99 TTFT (ms):                           348.99\n-----Time per Output Token (excl. 1st token)------\nMean TPOT (ms):                          7.80\nMedian TPOT (ms):                        7.76\nP99 TPOT (ms):                           8.09\n---------------Inter-token Latency----------------\nMean ITL (ms):                           7.79\nMedian ITL (ms):                         7.75\nP99 ITL (ms):                            8.50\n==================================================\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
